    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "\r\n\r\nCurrently there is no quit api in neovim. Clients (mostly qui) has to execute a \":qa\" command in order to securely quit without data loss (for example user closed window using mouse but there are unsaved changes in some files) and there is no event that reports it is safe to quit. What I want is an ```nvim_try_quit``` (or similar name) api function which does same thing with \":qa\" and a way to tell to the client that neovim is closed itself.\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/go-client/issues/139",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I think this is not desireable. There are to many edge cases. \n**For example the nvim-terminal has no `modified`-state.** \nA nvim_try_quit would then kill the terminal, even if the user has \"important\" things inside the term. \nThere is an open issue, where somebody complains excatly about this issue.\n\nThe user should be responsible what is going to be closed and what should be saved.\n\nIf you want to determinate open modified buffers, you can run `:buffers` and filter out everything that has not the `'+'` flag.\n\nIf you want a quicker generic closing function, that closes the current buffer/etc step by step, you can take a look at my way of doing it: I'm just firering my keymap to close what ever there is and if there is a modified buffer, it warns. (I don't care about the term-buffer)\n\n```lua\nvim.keymap.set('n', 'ßß', function()\n    if #vim.api.nvim_list_wins() == 1 and vim.bo[vim.api.nvim_win_get_buf(0)].buftype == 'quickfix' then vim.cmd('quit') end\n    if vim.bo.filetype == \"help\" then vim.cmd('bdelete') return end\n    if vim.bo.filetype == \"man\" then vim.cmd('bdelete') return end\n    if vim.bo.filetype == \"qf\" then vim.cmd('cclose') return end\n    if vim.bo.filetype == \"lf\" then vim.cmd('lclose') return end\n    if vim.bo.filetype == \"netrw\" then vim.cmd(\"bdelete\") return end\n    if vim.bo.filetype == \"vim\" and vim.bo.buftype == \"nofile\" then vim.cmd('quit') return end\n    if vim.bo.filetype == \"pager\" and vim.bo.buftype == \"nofile\" then vim.cmd('close') return end\n    if vim.bo.buftype == \"terminal\" then vim.cmd('bd!') return end\n    if not vim.bo.modified and #vim.fn.getbufinfo({ buflisted = 1 }) == 1 then vim.cmd('quit') end\n\n    pcall(vim.cmd.cclose())\n    if vim.bo.modified then\n        vim.api.nvim_echo({{ \"Buffer has unsaved changes!\", \"ErrorMsg\" }}, false, {})\n        return\n    end\n    if vim.o.diff == true then vim.cmd('qa') end\n\n    if #vim.fn.getbufinfo({ buflisted = 1 }) == 1 then\n        vim.cmd('quit')\n    else\n        vim.cmd('bdelete')\n    end\nend, { noremap = true })\n\n```\n\n\n",
